sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Lysis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Lambda Lysis Cassette genes required for cell lysis. Contains holin/anti-holin, endolysin, and rz / rz1 genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Ovadia

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K137127
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A81 Lac Promoter - Tight expression levels
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cox RS III, Surette MG, Elowitz MB. Programming gene expression with combinatorial promoters. Mol. Syst. Biol. 2007;3:145.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A lactose inducible promoter obtained from: Cox RS III, Surette MG, Elowitz MB. Programming gene expression with combinatorial promoters. Mol. Syst. Biol. 2007;3:145. Used for tight expression levels to maintain our lysis cassette genes. This allows the cell to lyse only when lactose is present, as for lysis at any other time may cause problems in our system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Ordered primers to PCR them out of the original plasmid, but they failed. Decided to order long primers and "dimerized" the promoter with restriction sites at the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Ovadia
